    "body": "In favour of generating the call to the 'print' function directly through nodes.\r\n\r\nMy reasoning was:\r\n* The utility code is not thread-safe in the freethreading build because it lazily caches the 'print' function and kwargs for a common argument combination.\r\n* While looking at that, I decided it would benefit from vectorcall too.\r\n\r\nI initially thought about rewriting it, but it seemed easier to use our existing vectorcall code generation and just do the transformation into Cython nodes.\r\n\r\nI think the only likely performance degredation is earlier limited api (without vectorcall) using the \"no newline\" syntax. This will now generate a keyword dict each time rather than caching it.",
