                "message": "Get rid of specialized print utility code\n\nIn favour of generating the call to the 'print' function\ndirectly through nodes.\n\nMy reasoning was:\n* The utility code is not thread-safe in the freethreading build\n  because it lazily caches the 'print' function and kwargs\n  for a common argument combination.\n* While looking at that, I decided it would benefit from vectorcall\n  too.\n\nI initially thought about rewriting it, but it seemed easier to\nuse out existing vectorcall code generation and just do the\ntransformation into Cython nodes.\n\nI think the only likely performance degredation is earlier limited\napi (without vectorcall) using the \"no newline\" syntax. This will\nnow generate a keyword dict each time rather than caching it.",
